  "text": "Loss of tolerogenic function has been reported in multiple APC subsets from NOD mice. First, CD8a 1 DCs (CD40 hi ) are defective at inducing CD4 1 T-cell tolerance after antigen delivery targeted to these DCs, but after CD40 blockade, they improve in their ability to mediate T-cell deletion and reduce Th1 stimulation [CITATION_1] . A deficiency of DCs to mediate T-cell deletion in PLNs was previously mapped to Idd3 (including Il2 and Acadl, underexpressed in stimulated NOD DCs) and Idd5 (Slc11a1, overexpressed in stimulated NOD DCs and MFs) (Supplementary Table 2 ) [CITATION_2] ",
